We're getting so many great stories that we've extended the deadline for your

Enron Business Extreme Enron entries to Wednesday, March 28!  Have no idea

what we're talking about?  Read on(

Enron employees are famous for taking risks.  Is this an ingrained

characteristic?  Are we natural-born adrenaline junkies?  We think so, but we

want to find out from you.

If your idea of a good vacation is training for the Eco-Challenge, driving

monster trucks or assisting archeological digs in Siberia, tell us all about

it.  If you know of an employee who has an unusual pastime like missionary

work in the Congo, chasing tornadoes or filming sharks, we want to know.

Send your entries by email to sarah.palmer@enron.com, by fax to 713-853-6790

or by mail to Sarah Palmer, Enron Public Relations, EB4703D, Houston, Texas

77002.

We'll choose our favorite extreme stories and publish them in the next issue

of Enron Business.  Also, don't forget to check out the current issue --

newly designed -- at http://home.enron.com/pubs/enronbiz/2001/vol1/index.htm
